children.name: SUCCESS_RESET_CONTENT
children.comment: The server has fulfilled the request and the user agent SHOULD reset the document view which caused the request to be sent. @see 205 Reset Content

children.name: SUCCESS_PARTIAL_CONTENT
children.comment: The server has fulfilled the partial GET request for the resource. @see 206 Partial Content

children.name: SUCCESS_OK
children.comment: The request has succeeded. @see 200 OK

children.name: SUCCESS_NON_AUTHORITATIVE_INFORMATION
children.comment: The returned metainformation in the entity-header is not the definitive set as available from the origin server, but is gatheredfrom a local or a third-party copy. @see 203 Non-Authoritative Information

children.name: SUCCESS_NO_CONTENT
children.comment: The server has fulfilled the request but does not need to return an entity-body, and might want to return updated metainformation. @see 204 No Content

children.name: SUCCESS_MULTI_STATUS
children.comment: Multiple resources were to be affected by the COPY, but errors on some of them prevented the operation from taking place. @see 207 Multi-Status

children.name: SUCCESS_IM_USED
SUCCESS_CREATED
children.comment: The request has been fulfilled and resulted in a new resource being created. @see 201 Created

children.name: SUCCESS_ALREADY_REPORTED
children.comment: Already Reported @see 208 Already Reported

children.name: SUCCESS_ACCEPTED
children.comment: The request has been accepted for processing, but the processing has not been completed. @see 202 Accepted

children.name: SERVER_ERROR_VARIANT_ALSO_NEGOTIATES
children.comment: The server has an internal configuration error: the chosen variant resource is configured to engage in transparent content negotiation itself, and is therefore not a proper end point in the negotiation process. @see 506 Variant Also Negotiates

children.name: SERVER_ERROR_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE
children.comment: The server is currently unable to handle the request due to a temporary overloading or maintenance of the server. @see 503 Service Unavailable

children.name: SERVER_ERROR_NOT_IMPLEMENTED
children.comment: The server does not support the functionality required to fulfill the request. @see 501 Not Implemented

children.name: SERVER_ERROR_NOT_EXTENDED
children.comment: The policy for accessing the resource has not been met in the request. @see 510 Not Extended

children.name: SERVER_ERROR_LOOP_DETECTED
children.comment: The server terminated an operation because it encountered an infinite loop while processing the request. @see 508 Loop Detected

children.name: SERVER_ERROR_INTERNAL
children.comment: The server encountered an unexpected condition which prevented it from fulfilling the request. @see 500 Internal Server Error

children.name: SERVER_ERROR_INSUFFICIENT_STORAGE
SERVER_ERROR_HTTP_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED
SERVER_ERROR_GATEWAY_TIMEOUT
children.comment: The server, while acting as a gateway or proxy, did not receive a timely response from the upstream server specified by the URI (e.g. HTTP, FTP, LDAP) or some other auxiliary server (e.g. DNS) it needed to access in attempting to complete the request. @see 504 Gateway Timeout

children.name: SERVER_ERROR_BAD_GATEWAY
children.comment: The server, while acting as a gateway or proxy, received an invalid response from the upstream server it accessed in attempting to fulfill the request. @see 502 Bad Gateway

children.name: REDIRECTION_USE_PROXY
children.comment: The requested resource MUST be accessed through the proxy given by the Location field. @see 305 Use Proxy

children.name: REDIRECTION_TEMPORARY_REDIRECT
children.comment: The requested resource resides temporarily under a different URI. @see 307 Temporary Redirect

children.name: REDIRECTION_SEE_OTHER
children.comment: The response to the request can be found under a different URI and SHOULD be retrieved using a GET method on that resource. @see 303 See Other

children.name: REDIRECTION_NOT_MODIFIED
REDIRECTION_MULTIPLE_CHOICES
children.comment: The requested resource corresponds to any one of a set of representations, each with its own specific location, and agent-driven negotiation information is being provided so that the user (or user agent) can select a preferred representation and redirect its request to that location. @see 300 Multiple Choices

children.name: REDIRECTION_MOVED_PERMANENTLY
children.comment: The requested resource has been assigned a new permanent URI and any future references to this resource SHOULD use one of the returned URIs. @see 310 Moved Permanently

children.name: REDIRECTION_FOUND
children.comment: The requested resource resides temporarily under a different URI. @see 302 Found

children.name: INFORMATIONAL_SWITCHING_PROTOCOLS
INFORMATIONAL_PROCESSING
children.comment: The server has accepted the complete request, but has not yet completed it. @see 102 Processing

children.name: INFORMATIONAL_CONTINUE
children.comment: The client SHOULD continue with its request. @see 100 Continue

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_UPGRADE_REQUIRED
children.comment: Allows a server to definitively state the precise protocol extensions given resource must be served with. @see 426 Upgrade Required

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA_TYPE
CLIENT_ERROR_UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY
children.comment: The server understands the content type of the request entity, and the syntax of the request entity is correct but was unable to process the contained instructions. @see 422 Unprocessable Entity

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED
children.comment: The request requires user authentication. @see 401 Unauthorized

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_REQUESTED_RANGE_NOT_SATISFIABLE
children.comment: Request included a Range request-header field, and none of the range-specifier values in this field overlap the current extent of the selected resource. @see 416 Requested Range Not Satisfiable

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_URI_TOO_LONG
children.comment: The server is refusing to service the request because the Request-URI is longer than the server is willing to interpret. @see 414 Request-URI Too Long

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_TIMEOUT
children.comment: The client did not produce a request within the time that the server was prepared to wait. @see 408 Request Timeout

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE
children.comment: The server is refusing to process a request because the request entity is larger than the server is willing or able to process. @see 413 Request Entity Too Large

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_PROXY_AUTHENTICATED
children.comment: The request requires user authentication. @see 407 Unauthorized

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_PRECONDITION_FAILED
children.comment: The precondition given in one or more of the request-header fields evaluated to false when it was tested on the server. @see 412 Precondition Failed

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_NOT_FOUND
children.comment: The server has not found anything matching the Request-URI. @see 404 Not Found

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_NOT_ACCEPTABLE
CLIENT_ERROR_METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED
children.comment: The method specified in the Request-Line is not allowed for the resource identified by the Request-URI. @see 405 Method Not Allowed

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_LOCKED
children.comment: The source or destination resource of a method is locked. @see 423 Locked

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_LENGTH_REQUIRED
children.comment: The server refuses to accept the request without a defined Content-Length. @see 411 Length Required

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_GONE
CLIENT_ERROR_FORBIDDEN
children.comment: The server understood the request, but is refusing to authorize it. @see 403 Bad Request

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_FAILED_DEPENDENCY
CLIENT_ERROR_EXPECTATION_FAILED
children.comment: The expectation given in an Expect request-header field could not be met by this server. @see 417 Expectation Failed

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_CONFLICT
children.comment: The request could not be completed due to a conflict with the current state of the resource. @see 409 Conflict

children.name: CLIENT_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST
children.comment: The request could not be understood by the server due to malformed syntax. @see 400 Bad Request
